Police are probing a case of culpable homicide after two police officers from Cato Manor SAPS were killed in a deadly crash on the M7, this morning. Police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, said: “It is alleged this morning at 04:30, two police officers stationed at Cato Manor detectives were driving on Edwin Swales Drive when their vehicle was struck by a truck which failed to stop at a set of robots. Both police officers aged 37 and 40 died at the scene. The circumstances surrounding the incident are being investigated by Bellair SAPS.” According to paramedic, Garrith Jamieson the truck driver was treated at the scene for his injuries and was transported to a hospital.